      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">52.222-33</ph> Notice of Requirement for Project Labor Agreement.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
         <p class="- topic/p " id="d3341e8">As prescribed in <ph class="- topic/ph " outputclass="ClauseProvisionXREF">
               <xref base="i1097603"
                     class="- topic/xref "
                     href="22.505.dita#FAR_22_505"
                     outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly">22.505</xref>(a)(1)</ph>, insert the following provision:</p>
         <p class="- topic/p " id="d3341e15" outputclass="Ctr_SmCaps">
            <ph rev="FAC 2024-02 January 22, 2024"><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2022–003?>Notice of Requirement for Project Labor Agreement (Jan 2024)<?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 52.222–33 by—   a. Revising the date of the provision;?></ph>
         </p>
         <ol class="- topic/ol " id="d3302e25">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d3341e21">
                  <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">(a)</ph>
                  <ph rev="FAC 2024-02 January 22, 2024"><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2022–003?>
                     <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Definitions</i>. As used in this provision, the following terms are defined in clause 52.222–34, Project Labor Agreement, of this solicitation “construction,” “labor organization,” “large-scale construction project,” and “project labor agreement.”<?FM MARKER [Why] b. Revising paragraphs (a) and (b);?></ph>
               </p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d3341e28">
                  <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">(b)</ph>
                  <ph rev="FAC 2024-02 January 22, 2024"><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2022–003?>Offerors shall—<?FM MARKER [Why] b. Revising paragraphs (a) and (b);?></ph>
               </p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d3341e33">
                  <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">(c)</ph>
                  <ph rev="FAC 2024-02 January 22, 2024"><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2022–003?>The project<?FM MARKER [Why] c. Removing from paragraph (c) introductory text “Consistent with applicable law, the project” and adding “The project” in its place;?></ph> labor agreement reached pursuant to this provision shall-</p>
               <ol class="- topic/ol " id="d3302e56">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d3341e39">
                        <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">(1)</ph> Bind the <ph rev="FAC 2024-02 January 22, 2024"><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2022–003?>Offeror and<?FM MARKER [Why] d. Removing from paragraph (c)(1) “offeror and all” and adding “Offeror and” in its place;?></ph> subcontractors engaged in construction on the construction project to comply with the project labor agreement;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d3341e44">
                        <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">(2)</ph> Allow the <ph rev="FAC 2024-02 January 22, 2024"><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2022–003?>Offeror<?FM MARKER [Why] e. Removing from paragraph (c)(2) “offeror” and adding “Offeror” in its place;?></ph> and all subcontractors to compete for contracts and subcontracts without regard to whether they are otherwise parties to collective bargaining agreements;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d3341e49">
                        <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">(3)</ph>
								                Contain guarantees against strikes, lockouts, and similar job disruptions;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d3341e54">
                        <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">(4)</ph>
								                Set forth effective, prompt, and mutually binding procedures for resolving labor disputes arising during the term of the project labor agreement;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d3341e59">
                        <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">(5)</ph>
								                Provide other mechanisms for labor-management cooperation on matters of mutual interest and concern, including productivity, quality of work, safety, and health; and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d3341e64">
                        <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">(6)</ph>
								                Fully conform to all statutes, regulations, Executive orders, and agency requirements.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d3341e69">
                  <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">(d)</ph> Any project labor agreement reached pursuant to this provision does not change the terms of <ph rev="FAC 2024-02 January 22, 2024"><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2022–003?>the resulting contract<?FM MARKER [Why] f. Removing from paragraph (d) “this contract” and adding “the resulting contract” in its place;?></ph> or provide for any price adjustment by the Government.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d3341e74">
                  <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">(e)</ph> The <ph rev="FAC 2024-02 January 22, 2024"><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2022–003?>Offeror<?FM MARKER [Why] g. Removing from paragraph (e) “offeror” and adding “Offeror” in its place;?></ph> shall submit to the Contracting Officer a copy of the project labor agreement with its offer.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
         <p class="- topic/p " outputclass="Endofprovision">(End of Provision)</p>
         <section class="- topic/section " outputclass="Alternate"><?FM MARKER [Alt] Start?>
            <p class="- topic/p " id="d3344e80">
               <ph rev="FAC 2024-02 January 22, 2024"><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2022–003?>
                  <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Alternate I </i>
                  <ph outputclass="SmCaps">(Jan 2024)</ph>. As prescribed in <ph outputclass="ClauseProvisionXREF" class="- topic/ph ">
                     <xref base="i1097603"
                           class="- topic/xref "
                           href="22.505.dita#FAR_22_505"
                           outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly">22.505</xref>
                  </ph>(a)(2), substitute the following paragraphs (b) and (e) for paragraphs (b) and (e) of the basic provision.<?FM MARKER [Why] h. In Alternate I:   i. Revising the date;   ii. Removing from the introductory text “22.505(a)(1)” and “clause” and adding “22.505(a)(2)” and “provision” in their places, respectively; and?></ph>
            </p>
            <p class="- topic/p " outputclass="List1" id="d3350e126">
               <ph rev="FAC 2024-02 January 22, 2024"><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2022–003?>(b) The apparent successful offeror shall—<?FM MARKER [Why] iii. Revising paragraph (b);?></ph>
            </p>
            <p class="- topic/p " outputclass="List2" id="d3350e131">
               <ph rev="FAC 2024-02 January 22, 2024">(1) Negotiate or become a party to a project labor agreement with one or more labor organizations for the term of the resulting construction contract; and</ph>
            </p>
            <p class="- topic/p " outputclass="List2" id="d3350e134">
               <ph rev="FAC 2024-02 January 22, 2024">(2) Require its subcontractors to become a party to the resulting project labor agreement.</ph>
            </p>
            <p class="- topic/p " outputclass="List1">(e) The apparent successful offeror shall submit to the Contracting Officer a copy of the project labor agreement prior to contract award.</p>
            <?FM MARKER [Alt] End?>
            <?FM MARKER [Alt] Start?>
            <p class="- topic/p " id="d3337e98">
               <ph rev="FAC 2024-02 January 22, 2024"><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2022–003?>
                  <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Alternate II </i>
                  <ph outputclass="SmCaps">(Jan 2024)</ph>. As prescribed in <ph outputclass="ClauseProvisionXREF" class="- topic/ph ">
                     <xref base="i1097603"
                           class="- topic/xref "
                           href="22.505.dita#FAR_22_505"
                           outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly">22.505</xref>
                  </ph>(a)(3), substitute the following paragraph (b) in lieu of paragraphs (b) through (e) of the basic provision:<?FM MARKER [Why] i. In Alternate II:   i. Revising the date;   ii. Removing from the introductory text “22.505(a)(2)” and “clause” and adding “22.505(a)(3)” and “provision” in their places, respectively; and?></ph>
            </p>
            <p class="- topic/p " outputclass="List1" id="d3350e154">
               <ph rev="FAC 2024-02 January 22, 2024"><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2022–003?>(b) If awarded the contract, the Offeror shall—<?FM MARKER [Why] iii. Revising paragraph (b); and?></ph>
            </p>
            <p class="- topic/p " outputclass="List2" id="d3350e159">
               <ph rev="FAC 2024-02 January 22, 2024">(1) Negotiate or become a party to a project labor agreement with one or more labor organizations for the term of the resulting construction contract; and</ph>
            </p>
            <p class="- topic/p " outputclass="List2" id="d3350e163">
               <ph rev="FAC 2024-02 January 22, 2024">(2) Require its subcontractors to become a party to the resulting project labor agreement.</ph>
            </p>
            <?FM MARKER [Alt] End?>
            <?FM MARKER [Alt] Start?>
            <p class="- topic/p " id="d3350e168"> <ph rev="FAC 2024-02 January 22, 2024"><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2022–003?> <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Alternate III </i> <ph outputclass="SmCaps">(Jan 2024)</ph>. As prescribed in <ph outputclass="ClauseProvisionXREF" class="- topic/ph "> <xref base="i1097603" class="- topic/xref " href="22.505.dita#FAR_22_505" outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly">22.505</xref> </ph>(a)(4), substitute the following paragraph (b) in lieu of paragraphs (b) through (e) of the basic provision:<?FM MARKER [Why] j. Adding Alternate III.?></ph> </p>
            <p class="- topic/p " outputclass="List1" id="d3350e181">
               <ph rev="FAC 2024-02 January 22, 2024">(b)(1) If awarded the contract, the Offeror may be required by the agency to negotiate or become a party to a project labor agreement with one or more labor organizations for the term of the order. The Contracting Officer will require that an executed copy of the project labor agreement be submitted to the agency—</ph>
            </p>
            <p class="- topic/p " outputclass="List3" id="d3350e184">
               <ph rev="FAC 2024-02 January 22, 2024">(i) With the order offer;</ph>
            </p>
            <p class="- topic/p " outputclass="List3" id="d3350e187">
               <ph rev="FAC 2024-02 January 22, 2024">(ii) Prior to award of the order; or</ph>
            </p>
            <p class="- topic/p " outputclass="List3" id="d3350e190">
               <ph rev="FAC 2024-02 January 22, 2024">(iii) After award of the order.</ph>
            </p>
            <p class="- topic/p " outputclass="List2" id="d3350e193">
               <ph rev="FAC 2024-02 January 22, 2024">(2) The Offeror shall require its subcontractors to become a party to the resulting project labor agreement for the term of the order.</ph>
            </p>
            <?FM MARKER [Alt] End?>
         </section>
